article.headline: Pennsylvania 105, Lafayette 73
article.story: PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Ibrahim Jaaber scored 21 points to lead five Penn players in double figures as the Quakers continued their high-scoring streak with a 105-73 victory over Lafayette on Monday night. Mark Zoller had 19 points and Eric Osmundson had 18 for Penn (9-5), which rolled up its highest total since scoring 114 points against Haverford in December 1993. The Quakers connected on 42-of-68 shots (62 percent) and have amassed 276 points in their last three outings. Andrew Brown had 16 points, including five 3-pointers, and Bilal Abdullah had 12 for the Leopards (8-8), who hit on 14-of-29 from beyond the arc. Penn trailed 8-2 early but then ran off 15 straight points and built a 53-34 advantage at halftime, connecting on 22-of-34 shots (65 percent) and forcing 15 Lafayette turnovers. The lead ballooned to 89-52 on a jumper by Jaaber with 8:52 remaining in the game. Penn has now defeated the Leopards five straight times and holds a 37-3 edge in the all-time series.
